name: Temur Sabertooth
oracle_text: {1}{G}: You may return another creature you control to its owner's hand. If you do, Temur Sabertooth gains indestructible until end of turn.
flavor_text:

—Crocodile Jackson, legendary cowboy

name: Pathbreaker Ibex
oracle_text: Whenever Pathbreaker Ibex attacks, creatures you control gain trample and get +X/+X until end of turn, where X is the greatest power among creatures you control.
flavor_text:
"Not only a wrecking ball, but a trendsetter in its own right."
—Crocodile Jackson, legendary cowboy

oracle_text:
Trample

flavor_text:

name: Ravenous Chupacabra
oracle_text: When Ravenous Chupacabra enters the battlefield, destroy target creature an opponent controls.
flavor_text:
"Why do these guys get such a bad rap? Is it the giant golden claws and teeth? The terrible stench? I think they're kinda cute."
—Crocodile Jackson, legendary cowboy

name: Mystical Tutor
oracle_text: Search your library for an instant or sorcery card, reveal it, then shuffle and put that card on top.
flavor_text: "Now, did I file that away under 'C' for 'Combo' or 'F' for 'Finisher?'"

name: Fact or Fiction
oracle_text: Reveal the top five cards of your library. An opponent separates those cards into two piles. Put one pile into your hand and the other into your graveyard.
flavor_text: Two futures unfurled before the mage, each rife with its own promise.

name: Fabricate
oracle_text: Search your library for an artifact card, reveal it, put it into your hand, then shuffle.
flavor_text: "I'll have just the right tool for the job!"

name: Counterspell
oracle_text: Counter target spell.
flavor_text: "If only there were a way to counter your inevitable whining."

name: Aether Gust
oracle_text: Choose target spell or permanent that's red or green. Its owner puts it on the top or bottom of their library.
flavor_text: The cleansing winds swept away all traces of the demon, until not even his legend remained.

name: Last-Minute Chopping
oracle_text: Ask target opponent if they remembered to get you a present. If they say yes, they put a card they own from outside the game into your hand. Otherwise, you gain control of target permanent they control.
flavor_text: "Dear brother, I couldn't forget you if I tried, and I *have* tried."
